The man’s body was found by the domestic worker and it is suspected criminals broke into the home in the early hours of Sunday morning. JOHANNESBURG – A man believed to be in his 80s has been found strangled to death in Lenasia, south of Johannesburg. It’s understood criminals broke into the elderly man’s home in the early hours of Sunday morning. His body was found by a domestic worker. The police’s Vincent Mashiteng says the motive for the murder is being investigated. “The police are investigating a case of murder, of an 80-year-old man that occurred in Lenasia Extension 5. The man was found dead in the lounge, by the domestic worker. We are still investigating whether there is anything missing in the house.” Mashiteng has urged anyone with information that could lead to the arrest of the suspects to contact the police.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)